physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Patient appeared well, afebrile. Cardiac examination revealed regular heart rate of 53 bpm, blood pressure 128/90 mm Hg, and an audible fourth heart sound, with a diffuse and laterally displaced apical impulse.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The heart rate of 200 bpm indicates a change from the 53 bpm noted later in examination.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Audible fourth heart sound and prominent second heart sound noted, with clear lungs on auscultation and no hepatosplenomegaly.

vital_signs.heart_rate: Asymptomatic at up to 150 bpm (during telemetry)

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Electrocardiogram showed sinus rhythm with multifocal atrial ectopic depolarizations and significant abnormalities including a short PR interval.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The initial 200 bpm heart rate was treated with electrical cardioversion, resulting in a stable sinus rhythm thereafter.
